{"TopicId":209557,"ForumId":107,"TopicTitle":"Why can\u0027t I attach fuel lines in EVA construction mode?","CreatedByName":"MAFman","CreatedById":101780,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-29T19:18:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MAFman","CreatedById":101780,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-29T19:18:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre my two vessels simply too far apart? I can attach one end of the line just fine but it refuses to let me attach the other end. What I\u0027m trying to do is connect my mining truck to my refinery using a fuel line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-08-29T19:20:37Z\u0022 title=\u002208/29/2022 07:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 29, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by MAFman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EDetails\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Echo__3","CreatedById":204997,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-30T01:58:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou cannot do what you are wanting in the stock game. You will need to connect the two crafts with docking ports or use the KLAW.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlternatively, you could use the fuel ducts from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-30T11:12:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u0027t need \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/108704-18x-dmagics-modlets-most-ksp-18-updates-10-29-2019/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EEVA Transfer from DMagics stash of modlets\u003C/a\u003E does exactly what you want.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}